# Security Rules

- **Never** hardcode API keys, tokens, or secrets in source files.
- API keys must come from `process.env` on the server side only.
- Never prefix env variables with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` if they contain secrets.
- Never log or return API key values in API responses (even partially).
- Always validate and sanitize user input before passing to LLM prompts.
- Always run `filterLLMOutput()` on Gemini responses before returning to client.

## Environment Variable Handling

- **Never** set env vars via interactive CLI commands (`vercel env add`, `heroku config:set`, etc.) — agent terminals are non-interactive and will silently save empty values.
- Always instruct the user to set env vars via the **platform dashboard** (Vercel dashboard, AWS console, etc.) or via their own interactive terminal.
- After env vars are changed, always redeploy (`vercel --prod`) to pick up the new values.
- To verify an env var is set correctly, use a temporary health-check endpoint or `vercel env pull` — never print the key value itself.
